About.Name: Cameren Banis
About.AboutText:
Hi, I am Cameren Banis. I am a passionate electrical engineering student with a keen interest in PCB design, power electronics, and control systems. Currently, I am pursuing my undergraduate degree at Seattle Pacific University. I am dedicated to expanding my knowledge and skills in various areas of electrical engineering, with a particular focus on power systems.

I enjoy working in a collaborative environment where I am able to tackle problems with my fellow peers, learning new things with every problem that arises.

Beyond the classroom, I am the acting IEEE chair at Seattle Pacific University, which allows me to explore various different fields in electrical engineering and learn about the evolving industry from their expertise. I believe in the importance of continuous learning and seek out opportunities to explore new technologies and methodologies.
